Trinity Gay died last week after being was caught in an exchange of gunfire between two vehicles. JOHANNESBURG US Olympic sprinter Tyson Gayhas thanked fans across the world for their support following the death of his 15-year-old daughter. Trinity Gay was killed last week after she was was caught in an exchange of gunfirebetween two vehicles outside a Kentucky restaurant. Mourners gathered at the Southland Christian Church on Saturday, where a funeral service was held. In a short video clip Gay says: I have received so much support, Trinity has received so much support and the family. I wanna say I love you guys and hopefully we can come together and stop the violence. Trinity would have wanted us to come together and have peace, and I am going to do whatever I can to help the youth. #LLT I JUST WANT TO THANK EVERYONE FOR THEIR SUPPORT AND PRAYERS. TRINITY A video posted by Tyson Gay (@tysonlgay) on Oct 22, 2016 at 2:51pm PDT #LLT I JUST WANT TO THANK EVERYONE FOR THEIR SUPPORT AND PRAYERS. TRINITYA video posted by Tyson Gay (@tysonlgay) on Oct 22, 2016 at 2:51pm PDT Four men have now been arrested in connection with the shooting.